column5: Cabellas and minn kota can't stop me from fishing.  Got out for eyes saturday and Monday..helps to live 20 minutes from the launch.  Saturday was slow, a dozen or so 24" pike released and 2 20" eyes.  It was cold most of the day too.    Monday was a bit better, starting off slow and progressing into double headers.  5 eyes 20 to 25" a bunch of small pike and a couple of smallmouth that went back I saved one pike because a friend asked me to bring him one.
There was a couple more pics sideways but I decided against posting 5lb OOS smallmouth pics
Thanks. It's nice to not have a slot size.
Nice going Dara thanks for the report and photos.
